    "explanation": "<p>Given the following parameters for machining cylindrical workpieces on a lathe:</p>\n\n<p><p><strong>Diameter of workpiece</strong>: 60 mm</p></p>\n<p><p><strong>Length of workpiece</strong>: 400 mm</p></p>\n<p><p><strong>Cutting speed (v)</strong>: 25 m/min</p></p>\n<p><p><strong>Feed (f)</strong>: 0.2 mm/rev</p></p>\n<p><p><strong>Taylor's tool life constant (C)</strong>: 75</p></p>\n<p><p><strong>Tool life exponent (n)</strong>: 0.25</p></p>\n<p><p><strong>Tool changing time (TCT)</strong>: 3 minutes</p></p>\n<p><p><strong>Labor and overhead cost</strong>: Rs. 5 per minute</p></p>\n\n<p>We are tasked with calculating the tool changing cost per piece. Here's a step-by-step explanation:</p>\n<p><strong>Tool Change Cost Calculation:</strong></p>\n\n<p><p><strong>Formula for tool change cost</strong>: </p>\n<p>$    \\text{Tool change cost} = z_1 \\times \\text{number of tool failures/piece} \\times \\text{TCT}    $</p></p>\n\n\n<p>Where $ z_1 = \\text{Rs. } 5 \\text{ per min.} $</p>\n\n\n<p><strong>Determine Number of Tool Failures per Piece</strong>:</p>\n\n\n<p><p><strong>Machining time $T_m$</strong>:</p>\n<p>$      T_m = \\frac{L}{f \\times N}       $</p>\n\n<p>$N = \\frac{1000 \\times v}{\\pi \\times D}$</p></p>\n<p><p>Substituting known values:</p>\n<p>$      T_m = \\frac{400}{0.2 \\times \\left(\\frac{1000 \\times 25}{\\pi \\times 60}\\right)} = \\frac{400 \\times \\pi \\times 60}{0.2 \\times 1000 \\times 25} \\approx 15.0857 \\text{ min}      $</p></p>\n\n\n<p><strong>Calculate Tool Life $T$</strong>:</p>\n\n\n<p><p>Formula for tool life:</p>\n<p>$      T = \\left(\\frac{c}{v}\\right)^{1/n}      $</p></p>\n<p><p>Substituting the values:</p>\n<p>$      T = \\left(\\frac{75}{25}\\right)^{1/0.25} = 81 \\text{ min}      $</p></p>\n\n\n<p><p><strong>Compute Number of Tool Failures per Piece</strong>:</p>\n<p>$    \\text{Number of tool failures/piece} = \\frac{T_m}{T} = \\frac{15.0857}{81} \\approx 0.1862    $</p></p>\n<p><p><strong>Calculate Tool Change Cost per Piece</strong>:</p>\n<p>$    \\text{Tool change cost per piece} = 5 \\times 0.1862 \\times 3 = \\text{Rs. } 2.7936    $</p></p>\n\n<p>Thus, the tool change cost per piece is approximately Rs. 2.79 (rounded to two decimal places).</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2025,
    "yearKey": "gate-me-2025",
    "difficulty": null
